author: Armisael7
body: $PAYC seems like a super solid choice for calls but that premium is really making me think it over

author: dvdmovie1
body: Well-run company, software and if you're a well-run Software as a Service/SaaS company in general (ADBE, PAYC, NOW, TEAM, AYX, etc etc etc etc) or one in an attractive vertical (VEEV, ANSS), you've done well over the last several years. SaaS names doing incredibly well this year - AYX up over 30% since January 1st. Even smaller companies in other countries - look at Nemetschek SE in Germany, up nearly 600% in the last 5 years.

author: dvdmovie1
body:
Elastic had a good quarter last night and is up today, but the concern over Amazon's competitive offering have been a cloud over it for a while now. It's a very interesting company but performance has been somewhat disappointing compared to peers.

I'd rather RNG, PAYC, AYX, EVBG, VEEV and a few others in terms of SaaS names. Zoom is certainly doing well because of current news (more downloads so far this year than all of last year, according to an analyst yesterday.)
